

## 🚀 Prometheus Setup on Ubuntu (via Minikube + Helm)

This guide helps you install **Minikube**, **Helm**, and **Docker**, and then deploy **Prometheus** on a local Kubernetes cluster.

---

### 🧰 1. Install Minikube

```bash
# Download the latest Minikube binary
curl -LO https://github.com/kubernetes/minikube/releases/latest/download/minikube-linux-amd64

# Install Minikube to /usr/local/bin and remove the downloaded file
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube && rm minikube-linux-amd64
```

**📝 What it does:**
Downloads and installs Minikube — a lightweight Kubernetes setup that runs locally.

---

### 🚀 2. Start Minikube and Verify Cluster

```bash
# Start the Minikube cluster
minikube start

# View all pods running across all namespaces
kubectl get po -A

# List all namespaces in the cluster
kubectl get ns -A
```

**📝 What it does:**

* Starts a local Kubernetes cluster
* Checks that everything is running properly

---

### ⚙️ 3. Install Helm (Kubernetes Package Manager)

```bash
# Install dependencies for Helm
sudo apt-get install curl gpg apt-transport-https --yes

# Add Helm’s official GPG key
curl -fsSL https://packages.buildkite.com/helm-linux/helm-debian/gpgkey | gpg --dearmor | sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/helm.gpg > /dev/null

# Add Helm repository to system sources
echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/helm.gpg] https://packages.buildkite.com/helm-linux/helm-debian/any/ any main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/helm-stable-debian.list

# Update packages and install Helm
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install helm -y
```

**📝 What it does:**
Installs **Helm**, which makes deploying apps like Prometheus much easier on Kubernetes.

---

### 📈 4. Install Prometheus via Helm

```bash
# Add the Prometheus community Helm repo
helm repo add prometheus-community https://prometheus-community.github.io/helm-charts

# Update repo list
helm repo update

# Install Prometheus in the cluster
helm install prometheus prometheus-community/prometheus
```

**📝 What it does:**
Downloads and installs Prometheus monitoring using Helm in your Minikube cluster.

---

### 🐳 5. Install Docker Engine

```bash
# Update system packages
sudo apt-get update

# Install required packages for Docker
sudo apt-get install ca-certificates curl -y

# Create a directory for Docker’s GPG key
sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings

# Download and add Docker’s GPG key
sudo curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc

# Add Docker’s official repository
echo \
  "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
  $(. /etc/os-release && echo "${UBUNTU_CODENAME:-$VERSION_CODENAME}") stable" | \
  sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null

# Update and install Docker components
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin -y
```

**📝 What it does:**
Sets up Docker from the official Docker repository with all the necessary plugins.

---

### 🔍 6. Verify Docker Installation

```bash
# Check Docker service status
sudo systemctl status docker

# Start Docker service if not running
sudo systemctl start docker

# Test Docker installation
sudo docker run hello-world
```

**📝 What it does:**
Ensures Docker is installed correctly and runs a test container.

---

### 🌐 7. Expose Prometheus Dashboard

```bash
# Forward Prometheus service port to host (accessible from browser)
kubectl port-forward service/prometheus 9090:80 --address=0.0.0.0
```

**📝 What it does:**
Makes Prometheus dashboard available at
👉 `http://<your-server-ip>:9090`

